Write a simple XML parser that assumes that attributes do not exist.  Given the following input from a text file, generate the following output:

Input:
<Person>
  <Fname>Mike</Fname>
  <Lname>Litman</Lname>
  <Age>15</Age>
  <Address>
    <Number>123</Number>
    <Street>Elm Street</Street>
    <City>Grafton</City>
    <State>WI</State>
    <Zip>53024</Zip>
  </Address>
</Person> 

Output:
Person ->
Fname -> Mike
Lname -> Litman
Age -> 15
Address ->
Number -> 123
Street -> Elm Street
City -> Grafton
State -> WI
Zip -> 53024
